abstract: It was the first time the former vice president expressed support for full impeachment. He had previously backed a congressional inquiry.
snippet: It was the first time the former vice president expressed support for full impeachment. He had previously backed a congressional inquiry.
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday called for President Trump’s impeachment for the first time, blistering Mr. Trump as a threat to American democracy and accusing him of “shooting holes in the Constitution.”

abstract: A feud between Coleen Rooney and Rebekah Vardy, the wives of noted English soccer stars, is playing out in the public sphere.
snippet: A feud between Coleen Rooney and Rebekah Vardy, the wives of noted English soccer stars, is playing out in the public sphere.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, Oct. 9, Americans awoke to the disheartening yet thrilling news that the celebrities had done it again — and this time it was war. The fields of battle were Twitter and Instagram, where Coleen Rooney accused Rebekah Vardy of leaking stories about her to the tabloids, and revealed that she had orchestrated a monthslong social media sting to catch Ms. Vardy in the act.

abstract: A series of internal State Department emails reflect diplomats’ frustration with the unexpected freeze on funding that Congress had already approved.
snippet: A series of internal State Department emails reflect diplomats’ frustration with the unexpected freeze on funding that Congress had already approved.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — American diplomats who had pushed for the Trump administration to restore security funding to Ukraine were advised by the White House to play down the release of the money when it was finally approved, documents show.

abstract: A quieter day in Washington provided a chance to look at how the still-nascent investigation is being received across the country.
snippet: A quieter day in Washington provided a chance to look at how the still-nascent investigation is being received across the country.
lead_paragraph: This morning’s episode of “The Daily” followed Representative Elissa Slotkin, a moderate Democrat, as she went to three forums in her mid-Michigan district — including one at the East Lansing pie bakery where I worked the 5 a.m. shift in high school! Her takeaway: Many voters want an investigation that feels deliberate. “There’s no need to come out of a meeting where you’ve heard some new testimony and just start talking to the press about how this seals the deal for you, and you’re done,” she said.

abstract: It once was clear what American businesses needed to avoid to succeed in China’s huge market. As the N.B.A. has shown, that’s no longer the case.

headline_main: China Is Now a Minefield for Western Companies

abstract: We need a Washington Corrupt Practices Act to stop political families from self-dealing.
snippet: We need a Washington Corrupt Practices Act to stop political families from self-dealing.
lead_paragraph: In 2016, JPMorgan Chase agreed to pay $264 million as part of a settlement with the federal government. The reason? An Asian subsidiary of the company had hired the children of Chinese government officials in the hopes of currying favor with their powerful parents — a violation of the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act.
